                    <floruit notBefore="1600" notAfter="1700">
                        The name Walda Krǝstos appears at the end of each stanza of the hymn 
                    ʾO-ʾƎgzǝʾǝtǝya Māryām stanzas. A similar name, 
                     ʾAbbā Walda Krǝstos, is explicitly credited as the author of a malkǝʿ hymn dedicated to 
                        ʾAbbā Nob. This strengthens the view that he was indeed a poet-monk 
                        responsible for composing hymns, including both ʾO-ʾƎgzǝʾǝtǝya Māryām and 
                        malkǝʿā ʾAbbā Nob.
                    </floruit>
